          This command allows you to search all selected files for a
     specified string, which may contain wildcards.  If a match is found,
     you are told which file contains the string, and you are given the
     option to enter the text viewer and read the file.  If you opt to do
     this, a search for the string is automatically initiated once the file
     has been read by the text viewer.

          If any directories are selected, all the files within those
     directories are also searched.

          The flags ucnlc, wild and byword are off by default.


     ARexx Results:

